@Kami thanks for reviewing this. I got an email from Matt Sticker (boards@gmail.com) asking me to re-upload my key to keys.openpgp.org. Here's the full text of the email:

> Due to a recently disclosed protocol vulnerability in PGP keyservers, we've temporarily switched to using a safer variant at keys.openpgp.org. While this site does mirror (most) of the general public keys out there, I'm not sure how long it takes. Can you try uploading your key directly there?

I was going to ask and confirm about this process before I did what the email asked. Should I go ahead and re-upload my key to that site?

@PrinceSydney Thanks again for the contribution. I finally had a chance to review it today.

Overall, the PR looks like a great start, but there are some small things which still need to be improved or fixed.

Once those comments are addressed, please also make sure the build passes (it looks like it's failing now).

@PrinceSydney just a heads up - a5a79a6, b545797.

I missed that during the review.

Encoding data inside the driver class would work as far as drive functionality is concerned, but it doesn't follow the Libcloud way of serializing request data and as such, it would break things like the debug functionality - https://libcloud.readthedocs.io/en/latest/troubleshooting.html#debugging
